## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent and comprehensive data on the effectiveness of carbon credits. Many studies focus on specific projects or regions, which may not be representative of the global situation. Additionally, the rapidly evolving nature of climate policy and market mechanisms means that findings can quickly become outdated. Further research is needed to evaluate long-term impacts and improvements in the carbon credit system.